{"title_page": "Master (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|2020 film directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Master\n| image          = Master Third Look Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Third look poster\n| director       = [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]]\n| producer       = Xavier Britto\n| writer         = [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]]<br/>Rathna Kumar<br/>Pon Parthiban\n| starring       = [[ Vijay (actor)|Vijay ]]<br>[[Vijay Sethupathi ]]<br>[[Malavika Mohanan]]<br>[[Andrea Jeremiah]]\n| music          = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cinematography = [[Sathyan Sooryan]]\n| editing        = [[Philomin Raj]]\n| studio         = XB Film Creators\n| distributor    = Seven Screen Studio\n| released       = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n}}\n'''''Master''''' is an upcoming 2020 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action-thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/team-thalapathy-64-off-to-mumbai-second-schedule-shoot-begins-6098388/ |title=Team Master arrives in Mumbai; second schedule begins |date=November 2019 |website=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Andrea\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijays-thalapathy-64-adds-andrea-jeremiah-gouri-g-kishan-to-cast/article29843068.ece/amp/ |title=Vijay's 'Master' adds Andrea Jeremiah, Gouri G Kishan to cast |date=31 October 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/vijay-s-thalapathy-64-launched-with-a-puja-ceremony-see-pic/story-vNYnZtFqh4Nkhao5wN2qQI.html |title=Vijay's Thalapathy 64 launched with a puja ceremony, see pic |date=3 Oct 2019 |website=Hindustan Times |language=en |access-date=7 November 2019}}</ref> written and directed by [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]], and produced by Xavier Britto. The film stars actors [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and [[Vijay Sethupathi]] playing the lead roles with an ensemble cast. The music for the film composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]] while cinematography and editing are handled by [[Sathyan Sooryan]] and [[Philomin Raj]] respectively.\n\nThe film has been postponed due to [[Covid-19]] [[pandemic]]. The film will be released in languages Tamil, Telugu and Hindi.\n\nThe film will be the Hindi release for Vijay as he has also fan following in North India.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] as John Durairaj  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/vijays-character-name-in-master-revealed/articleshow/74686613.cms|title=Vijay's character name in Master revealed!|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n* [[Vijay Sethupathi]] as Bhavani, a notorious criminal<ref> name=web>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/thalapathy-64-first-look-poster-vijays-next-is-titled-master/articleshow/73047407.cms|title=Thalapathy 64 first look poster: Vijay's next is titled 'Master'|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n* [[Malavika Mohanan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/thalapathy-64-actress-malavika-mohanan-jets-off-on-a-vacation-after-wrapping-up-fight-scenes-with-co-star-vijay-sethupathi/articleshow/73007202.cms|title=Thalapathy 64 actress Malavika Mohanan jets off on a vacation after wrapping up fight scenes with co-star Vijay Sethupathi \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n* [[Andrea Jeremiah]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/291019/andrea-joins-thalapathy-64.html|title=Andrea joins Thalapathy Yogi Babu 64|first=Anupama|last=Subramanian|date=30 October 2019|website=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref>\n* [[Shanthanu Bhagyaraj]]<ref name=\"STOI\">{{cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/shanthnu-bhagyaraj-to-join-thalapathy-64/articleshow/71391508.cms |title=Shanthnu Bhagyaraj to join Thalapathy 64? \u2013 Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Arjun Das]]<ref name=\"Das\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/thalapathy-64-antony-varghese-out-kaithi-star-arjun-das-hops-on-board-1624110-2019-12-01|title=Master (2020 film): Antony Varghese out, Kaithi star Arjun Das hops on board|website=India Today}}</ref>\n*[[Ramya Subramanian]]<ref name=web>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/thalapathy-64-first-look-poster-vijays-next-is-titled-master/articleshow/73047407.cms|title=Thalapathy 64 first look poster: Vijay's next is titled 'Master'|website=The Times of India}}</ref> \n* [[Nassar(actor)|Nassar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/nassar-to-play-the-role-of-a-senior-professor-in-thalapathy-64/articleshow/72870699.cms|title=Nassar to play the role of a senior professor in 'Thalapathy 64'? \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> \n* [[Dheena (actor)|Dheena]]<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/comedian-dheena-to-join-vijays-thalapathy64/articleshow/72488992.cms Comedian Dheena to join Vijay\u2019s Thalapathy64 | Tamil Movie News \u2013 Times of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com (12 December 2019). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref>\n* [[Sanjeev (Tamil actor)|Sanjeev]]<ref name=\"web\" />\n* [[Srinath (actor)|Srinath]]<ref name=\"web\" />\n* [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]]<ref name=\"web\" />\n* [[Nagendra Prasad]]<ref>[https://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/83726/cinema/Kollywood/Nagendra-Prasad---Vijay-together-after-15years.htm 15 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0baf\u0bcd \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bc7\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0